About:
Nestled on Hobart’s pristine waterfront, Huon Quays is truly outstanding, presenting amazing views of the Derwent River and Hobart’s landmark Derwent Bridge. Huon Quays offers a relaxed surrounding with a stunning outlook and delivering all these unique qualities just minutes from the CBD in Hobart.
 
 
Huon Quays location and versatility lends itself to all types of functions and is the perfect setting for corporate functions and training with large exhibition and display areas, theatre performances, promotions, product launches, gala dinners, school formals, cocktail parties, charity balls, trade shows, fashion shows, sporting functions, birthday parties, dance and music festivals or be the theatre for your most memorable and special event of your lifetime, your wedding.
 
 
The venue has a capacity of 600 guest’s theatre style and up to 250 for a sit down function. It can be divided for a more intimate gathering.

Maps URL: http://maps.google.com/maps?q=Salamanca Place, Hobart, Tas, 7000(Plan B)
About:
The newest club night on the Salamanca strip is a NO COMPROMISE affair for SERIOUS UNDERGROUND dance music enthusiasts... ONLY!

Located above Syrup Nightclub, PLAN B is completely removed from the regular Syrup nightclub. With a separate alleyway entrance, separate queuing away from all the bogans, and a SUPER-STRICT ENTRY POLICY means that this is a dance music nirvana for all those who LOVE their underground sounds!

From dirty Electro to brutal Dubstep, upfront House and the slammin'est Drum n Bass, PLAN B will provide your weekly dose of illicit sounds, cooked up by the cream of Hobart's DJs and Producers. The strict music policy also means is 100% quality electronic music, 100% of the time!! No rubbish Top 40 here!!

With the 10,000 watt soundsystem pumping only the crispest underground sounds, and our intelligent lighting system, PLAN B will give your Aural and Visual senses the highest of highs.
